#   GET-024: `be get ?#<sha>` records a DETACHED cur-tip (`?<sha>`) instead of trunk-state ‚Äî breaks `be put ?#<sha>` + commit (POSTDET). Regression from GET-023.

`?#<sha>` (empty query + `#`-fragment sha) means "current/trunk branch, pinned to
state <sha>" ‚Äî a NON-detached trunk-state checkout you can commit on top of. But the
[[GET-023]] checkout arm canonicalises it into the DETACHED form `?<sha>` (query=sha,
empty fragment) when it records the cur-tip, so a follow-up `be post` is refused
POSTDET ("detached wt ‚Äî re-attach to a branch"). Real regression from `d6f35358`,
caught by `be-put-06-triangle` (SSH-gated, so it slipped the build-debug merge checks).
Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Symptom: `test/put/06-triangle` round R4 (`be put "?#$TIP"` ‚Üí `be get --force "?#$TIP"`
    ‚Üí `be post`) dies at the post with `sniff: post: refusing on detached wt ‚Ä¶ Error: POSTDET`.
    PASSES on parent `b71eba2a`, FAILS 3/3 on `d6f35358`/`ef8901fa` (clean trunk,
    `-DWITH_SSH=ON`). Not flaky, not a stale-wt artifact (main wt cur == trunk tip).
 -  Root cause: [[GET-023]] (`d6f35358`) added the `?#<sha>` arm at `sniff/GET.c` (the
    `has_q && $empty(query) && !$empty(fragment)` branch + its `~:2175` source compose)
    that builds the GETCheckout SOURCE in the DETACHED form `?<frag>` (`u8csMv(fsrc_u.query,
    frag)`, empty fragment) ‚Üí the cur-tip wtlog row lands as `?<sha40>`. `post_is_detached_wt`
    (`sniff/POST.c:945`, DIS-009) flags empty-fragment + 40-hex-query as detached ‚Üí POST
    refuses. The input was `?#<sha>` (TRUNK-STATE, fragment-sha) ‚Äî it must NOT collapse to
    the detached query-sha form.
 -  Spec: PUT (`PUT.html` ¬ßPUT) ‚Äî `be put ?#<sha>` is a legitimate trunk reset that allows a
    follow-up commit. The detached `?<sha>` form (DIS-009) staying detached is CORRECT; only
    the `?#<sha>` mis-canonicalisation is wrong.
 -  PROCESS GAP: the GET-023 merge built only `build-debug` (no `WITH_SSH`), so the
    SSH-gated `be-put-06-triangle` never ran ‚Üí the regression landed green-looking.

### Goals
 -  `be get ?#<sha>` checks out `<sha>` and records the cur-tip as TRUNK-STATE (`?#<sha>`:
    empty query + `#`-fragment), NON-detached ‚Äî a follow-up `be post` is allowed.
 -  Preserve GET-023's classify-or-reject (invalid fragment ‚Üí error; `SNIFFfragref` green)
    AND the genuine detached `?<sha>` form staying detached.

### Constraints
 -  Fix in the GET-023 `sniff/GET.c` arm: record the source as the trunk-state form
    (empty query + fragment=frag), NOT the detached `?<frag>` ‚Äî reuse `u`'s parsed
    components rather than re-composing a query-sha. No re-roll of URI handling.
 -  VALIDATE with `-DWITH_SSH=ON` (build-ssh) ‚Äî `be-put-06-triangle` is the repro; it MUST
    pass. Full `ctest` green in BOTH build-debug and build-ssh.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  (open) The arm passes `?<frag>` as the GETCheckout source; change it to the
    `?#<frag>` (trunk-state) shape so the recorded cur-tip keeps an empty query + the sha
    in the fragment ‚Äî exactly what `post_is_detached_wt` treats as NON-detached.

